      "writtenOn": "2018-12-27T16:00:33Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m not thrilled with the performance implications of this. Looking back, we were doing one float-to-byte per vertex before, plus a conditional integer scaling trick to fold it into the color.\n\nNow we\u0027re doing floating point scaling, with a conditional packing to bytes or half-floats.\n\nIt really seems like we\u0027d be better off doing the folding of coverage into color in the vertex shader, at the cost of the coverage attribute?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 39,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 93
      },
      "revId": "6413d15209a0724c1b6851eaeb6e6849fc556194",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "95a84b96_484fb26a",
        "filename": "src/gpu/ops/GrAALinearizingConvexPathRenderer.cpp",
