      "writtenOn": "2018-12-27T18:31:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "From the benchmarking I did, fp32x4 attributes are quite a bit more expensive than fp16x4 (which are slightly more expensive than the unormx4). Especially if we only need to do the packing once per path - which would be the case if we weren\u0027t folding in coverage here.\n\nI\u0027ll investigate, I think I\u0027d have to add some extra logic to the default GP (flag that says to combine the coverage in the vertex shader even when it\u0027s supplied as an attribute).",
